prepareForCommunication

public java.util.Map<java.net.InetSocketAddress,Channel> prepareForCommunication(java.util.List<Party> listOfParties,
                                                                                 KeyExchangeProtocol keyExchange,
                                                                                 SecurityLevel securityLevel,
                                                                                 ConnectivitySuccessVerifier successLevel,
                                                                                 long timeOut)
The main function of the class. This function is also the only public function in the class. An application that wants to use the communication layer will call this function in order to prepare for communication after providing the required parameters. This function initiates the creation of the final actual socket connections between the parties. If this function succeeds, the application may use the send and receive functions of the created channels to pass messages.

Parameters:
listOfParties - the original list of parties to connect to
keyExchange - the key exchange algorithm protocol to use after a channel is connected
securityLevel - the required security level for all the connections. E.g Plain, encrypted, authenticated or secured
successLevel - the ConnectivitySuccessVerifier algorithm to use
timeOut - the maximum amount of time we allow for the connection stage
Returns:
true if the success function has succeeded and false otherwise
